.SH "NAME"
sepermit.conf \- configuration file fo' tha pam_sepermit module
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Da linez of tha configuration file have tha followin syntax:
.PP
\fI<user>\fR[:\fI<option>\fR:\fI<option>\fR\&.\&.\&.]
.PP
The
\fBuser\fR
can be specified up in tha followin manner:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
a username
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
a groupname, with
\fB@group\fR
syntax\&. This should not be trippin wit netgroups\&.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
a SELinux user name with
\fB%seuser\fR
syntax\&.
.RE
.PP
Da recognized options are:
.PP
\fBexclusive\fR
.RS 4
Only single login session is ghon be allowed fo' tha user n' tha user\*(Aqs processes is ghon be capped on logout\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBignore\fR
.RS 4
Da module aint NEVER gonna return PAM_SUCCESS status fo' tha user\&. Well shiiiit, it will return PAM_IGNORE if SELinux is up in tha enforcin mode, n' PAM_AUTH_ERR otherwise\&. Well shiiiit, it is useful if you wanna support passwordless hommie playas n' other confined playas wit passwordz simultaneously\&.
.RE
.PP
Da lines which start wit # characta is comments n' is ignored\&.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.PP
These is some example lines which might be specified in
/etc/security/sepermit\&.conf\&.
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
%guest_u:exclusive
%staff_u:ignore
%user_u:ignore
    
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
